      "highlights" : "The weather conditions fostered a strengthening of the snowpack in particular on very steep sunny slopes.",
      "comment" : "In steep terrain there is a danger of falling on the hard snow surface. In all altitude zones hardly any more moist and wet avalanches are to be expected as the temperature drops. <br/> <br/> Weak layers exist deeper in the snowpack. Single winter sport participants can release avalanches in isolated cases. These can be triggered in deep layers and reach large size. These avalanche prone locations are barely recognisable, even to the trained eye. <br/> <br/> Thus far only isolated gliding avalanches are possible. In addition the wind slabs at high altitudes and in high Alpine regions are capable of being triggered in very isolated cases."
