      "comment" : "Towards its surface, the snowpack is largely stable and its surface has a melt-freeze crust that is strong in many cases. <br/> 2 to 10 cm of snow will fall above approximately 1600 m. Up to 20 cm in areas bordering Piedmont. <br/> Especially steep shady slopes high altitudes and the high Alpine regions: Weak layers exist in the old snowpack. <br/> Adjacent to ridgelines and in pass areas snow depths vary greatly, depending on the infuence of the wind."
